    "The second type of extensions that we treat in this paper is of fields close to an algebraically closed field, meaning that they are obtained by cutting out of an algebraic closure of K as the fixed subfield by finitely many automorphisms σ 1,.",
    "Fix an algebraic closure K of any field K and let K sep be the separable closure of K in K. Let G K be the absolute Galois group Gal(K sep /K) of K and e a positive integer.",
    "For any σ = (σ 1,.",
    ", σ e) ∈ G e K (the direct product of e copies of G K), set K(σ) to be the fixed field of σ in K. We also set K[σ] to be the maximal Galois subextension of K in K(σ).",
    "We equip the compact group G e K with the normalized Haar measure µ = µ G e K, which allows G e K to be regarded as a probability space [FriJ23, Section 21.1]."
